label: publication moratorium
description: This requirement indicates that requestor agrees not to publish results of studies until a specific date; DUO:0000024

label: data use requirements
description: Requirements indicate additional conditions set for use.; DUO:0000017

label: user specific restriction
description: This requirement indicates that use is limited to use by approved users.; DUO:0000026

label: time limit on use
description: This requirement indicates that use is approved for a specific number of months.; DUO:0000025

label: institution specific restriction
description: This requirement indicates that use is limited to use within an approved institution.; DUO:0000028

label: project specific restriction
description: This requirement indicates that use is limited to use within an approved project.; DUO:0000027

label: return to database or resource
description: This requirement indicates that the requestor must return derived/enriched data to the database/resource.; DUO:0000029

label: method development
description: An investigation concerning development of methods, algorithms, software or analytical tools.; DUO:0000031

label: ancestry research
description: An investigation concerning ancestry or population origins.; DUO:0000033

label: population research
description: An investigation concerning a specific population group.; DUO:0000032

label: gender category research
description: An investigation concerning specific gender categories.; DUO:0000035

label: age category research
description: An investigation concerning specific age categories.; DUO:0000034

label: biomedical research
description: An investigation concerning health, medical, or biomedical research.; DUO:0000037

label: research control
description: An investigation concerning use of data as reference or control material.; DUO:0000036

label: drug development research
description: Biomedical research concerning drug development.; DUO:0000039

label: genetic research
description: Biomedical research concerning genetics (i.e., the study of genes, genetic variations and heredity).; DUO:0000038

label: disease category research
description: Biomedical research research concerning specific disease/s; DUO:0000040

label: general research use
description: This primary category consent code indicates that use is allowed for general research use for any research purpose.; DUO:0000042

label: consent code primary category
description: A categorical data item indicating the primary category the consent code belongs to according to Dyke et al. 2016.; DUO:0000002

label: consent code
description: A data item that is used to indicate consent permissions for datasets and/or materials, and relates to the purposes for which datasets and/or material might be removed, stored or used.; DUO:0000001

label: no restriction
description: This consent code primary category indicates there is no restriction on use.; DUO:0000004

label: consent code secondary category
description: A categorical data item indicating the secondary category the consent code belongs to according to Dyke et al. 2016.; DUO:0000003

label: health or medical or biomedical research
description: This primary category consent code indicates that use is allowed for health/medical/biomedical purposes; does not include the study of population origins or ancestry.; DUO:0000006

label: general research use and clinical care
description: This primary category consent code indicates that use is allowed for health/medical/biomedical purposes and other biological research, including the study of population origins or ancestry.; DUO:0000005

label: disease specific research
description: This primary category consent code indicates that use is allowed provided it is related to the specified disease.; DUO:0000007

label: population origins or ancestry research
description: This primary category consent code indicates that use of the data is limited to the study of population origins or ancestry.; DUO:0000011

label: research specific restrictions
description: This secondary category consent code indicates that use is limited to studies of a certain research type.; DUO:0000012

label: no general methods research
description: This secondary category consent code indicates that use includes methods development research(e.g., development of software or algorithms) only within the bounds of other use limitations.; DUO:0000015

label: research use only
description: This secondary category consent code indicates that use is limited to research purposes (e.g., does not include its use in clinical care).; DUO:0000014

label: genetic studies only
description: This secondary category consent code indicates that use is limited to genetic studies only (i.e., no phenotype-only research); DUO:0000016

label: publication required
description: This requirement indicates that requestor agrees to make results of studies using the data available to the larger scientific community.; DUO:0000019

label: not for profit use only
description: This requirement indicates that use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations and not-for-profit use, non-commercial use.; DUO:0000018

label: collaboration required
description: This requirement indicates that the requestor must agree to collaboration with the primary study investigator(s).; DUO:0000020

label: geographical restriction
description: This requirement indicates that use is limited to within a specific geographic region.; DUO:0000022

label: ethics approval required
description: This requirement indicates that the requestor must provide documentation of local IRB/ERB approval.; DUO:0000021
